folder: Irving Place - Between 14th and 15th Streets (East)., Manhattan, NY
text:
A general view eastward from the Consolidated Edison Building, at 2-4 Irving Place, east side, from East 14th to East 15th Streets, showing East 14th Street (right) and East 15th Street (center). The cleared area is Stuyvesant Park, bounded by East 15th and East 17th Streets, Rutherford and Livingston Places. On the northeastern edge of the park is seen Beth-Israel Hospital at the S.E. corner of Livingston Place and East 17th Street and (left) St. George Church (P.E.) at the N.W. corner of Rutherford Place and East 16th Street. In the background is discernible the East River and the Brooklyn shore.

October 31, 1932.

Wurtz Brothers.
title: General view - [Manhattan - Irving Place - Between 14th and 15th Streets (East).]
